<h3 class="date"><a href="/2008/oct/12/">&#x27a0;</a> October 12, 2008</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="a912rtag9" >

        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://www.google.com/search?q=a912rtag9">a912rtag9?</a></h4>

        
            
        

        <p>Since breaking the search box on groovymother a couple of weeks ago, I&#8217;ve spotted a lot of XSS attempts in my logs.  The phrase &#8220;a912rtag9&#8221; in particular seems to appear a lot, and it looks like it&#8217;s a bot spidering search boxes across the internet. Anyone know its origin? UPDATED TO ADD: Looks like it&#8217;s Yahoo&#8217;s Slurp Bot making these requests! Also, the Googlebot is searching for &#8220;a912rtag6&#8221;. (And yes, I&#8217;ve verified the IP addresses) How odd!</p>

        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span10">
                
